    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">Using LLMs to Summarize Long Blog Drafts</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>In this post, I examined how an LLM can be used to summarize a long blog draft into a concise overview. When posts grow longer through revision, it can become difficult to clearly articulate the main takeaway.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>Rather than summarizing manually, I used the model to distill the core argument while preserving the original intent of the post.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">The Graphic</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "<img src=\"image.png\" alt=\"LLM summarizing a long blog draft\" width=\"60%\">\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Draft Excerpt</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "Large language models can assist writers at multiple stages of the blogging process, from brainstorming ideas to revising drafts. However, their effectiveness depends on how intentionally they are used. Without clear goals, LLM outputs can become unfocused or overly generic, which may weaken the overall message of a post.\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Prompt</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "Summarize this excerpt in one or two sentences while preserving its main point.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Response</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "LLMs can support blogging at many stages, but their usefulness depends on intentional use. Without clear goals, their outputs may become generic and weaken a postâ€™s overall message.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>The summary captured the central idea without introducing new claims. It made the main takeaway clearer and more immediately accessible.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">Reflection</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>This experiment showed how useful LLMs can be for clarifying the core message of a post. Seeing a condensed version helped me evaluate whether the draft was staying focused.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>For blogging, this is especially helpful when writing introductions, conclusions, or summaries for readers who may not read the entire post.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>Overall, this use case reinforced that LLMs are effective tools for synthesis and clarity, not just content generation.</p>\n",
    "g"
   ]
